name: DINO DISCOVERIES: pterodactyl
description: Second dino comin up, PTERODACTYL the winged beast. According to Samanthi, on June 3rd 2021: PTERODACTYL is a genus that includes winged reptiles with teeth. On the other hand, PTERANODON is a genus that includes winged reptiles without teeth. What's the next dino? Stay tuned people!
